614
00:43:08,899 --> 00:43:09,170
Rym: Absolutely.

615
00:43:09,410 --> 00:43:11,989
Scott: I mean, for for public play, right?

616
00:43:12,290 --> 00:43:19,429
Scott: The protection by making that the only communication mechanism, which is like what Hearthstone did, where you can only say like six things or whatever, right?

617
00:43:19,831 --> 00:43:23,030
Scott: It provides a great protection against abuse and harassment.

618
00:43:23,751 --> 00:43:33,030
Scott: And if the menu choices are, you know, vast enough, you're not losing that much in terms of, you know, team communication.

619
00:43:34,792 --> 00:43:43,130
Scott: But if you're doing a serious competitive game, right, like real esports championship, then it's like, yeah, you need to actually just be able to fully talk to people.

620
00:43:44,151 --> 00:43:46,910
Scott: It's not going to cut it, but that's not most cases.

621
00:43:47,151 --> 00:43:47,788
Scott: So what's the big deal?

622
00:43:48,390 --> 00:43:56,049
Rym: Now, it's interesting because this leads to a situation that I've seen in Overwatch where I prefer to play with people who have voice on.

623
00:43:56,370 --> 00:43:57,530
Rym: Like, it's just easier to communicate.

624
00:43:57,710 --> 00:43:59,230
Rym: It's easier to coordinate, like, whatever.

625
00:43:59,310 --> 00:43:59,670
Rym: That's fine.

626
00:43:59,952 --> 00:44:01,190
Rym: I only play competitive anyway.

627
00:44:02,972 --> 00:44:09,117
Rym: But if you join a game with randos as opposed to coming in with a team, there might be a few people on your team.

628
00:44:09,137 --> 00:44:10,510
Rym: for whatever reason, just don't join voice.

629
00:44:10,891 --> 00:44:12,669
Rym: Maybe they join and listen, even if they don't talk.

630
00:44:12,953 --> 00:44:13,946
Rym: Maybe they don't join at all.

631
00:44:14,950 --> 00:44:16,100
Scott: Maybe they have good reasons, right?

632
00:44:17,570 --> 00:44:18,768
Scott: Maybe they can't talk.

633
00:44:19,450 --> 00:44:41,270
Scott: Maybe they have a voice that has an accent or a tone or a pitch that would result in them receiving harassment and they don't want to expose some information about themselves that would be garnished or whatever through just hearing their voice.

634
00:44:42,091 --> 00:44:47,469
Scott: Or even maybe they don't have the technological capabilities or sophistication to set it up.

635
00:44:47,850 --> 00:44:52,210
Scott: Maybe there is sounds in their house around them they don't want anyone hearing.

636
00:44:52,690 --> 00:44:57,989
